Note on derivative builds:

This repository contains only:
  1. Original Rust tooling (warp-zh-extractor, warp-zh-builder) — MIT, this license.
  2. Standalone Python batch-translation scripts (tools/translations/kit/) — MIT, this license.
  3. A translation table (translations/strings.json) and glossary
     (translations/glossary.json) — original work of this repository's
     contributors, MIT, this license.

Running `warp-zh-builder` produces a localized copy of Warp under
`build/warp-zh/`. That output is a derivative work of the upstream Warp
source (https://github.com/warpdotdev/Warp), which is licensed under AGPLv3
and MIT. The output therefore remains subject to upstream Warp's licenses;
the MIT license above does NOT relicense Warp itself.
